Dataset downloaded from: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/shawon10/ckplus

About dataset:

In this dataset, emotions are represented as images of 48x48px. When downloading, we got 3 copies of each emotion, so in Python we can run this command to delete reduntand images:

import os
import shutil

ckp_directory = 'datasets/ck+/'

for emotion_folder in os.listdir(ckp_directory):
    emotion_path = os.path.join(ckp_directory, emotion_folder)

    if os.path.isdir(emotion_path):
        image_files = os.listdir(emotion_path)

        image_files.sort()

        for i in range(0, len(image_files)):
            if i % 3 != 0:
                image_to_delete = os.path.join(emotion_path, image_files[i])

                os.remove(image_to_delete)


Emotions are defined as determined index below:

    0 : anger (45 samples)
    1 : neutral (18 samples)
    2 : disgust (59 samples)
    3 : fear (25 samples)
    4 : happy (69 samples)
    5 : sadness (28 samples)
    6 : surprise (83 samples)


